content: I liked the story but I wouldn't get into it the series isn't complete and I doubt they will

I've enjoyed both episodes that are available so far. Yes they are typos, yes sometimes the grammar doesn't line up quite right but what do you expect with a story that you can alter each time you read it? There are not enough of these to have an effect on the enjoyment of reading and playing through the story. I am looking forward to the next episode!

A required read for anyone even slightly interested in interactive fiction. A true shining beacon that convinced me that there is limitless untapped potential in interactive fiction that no one except Zachery Sergi(this book's auther) and one or two others have come close to

A gripping and compelling interactive novel with political intrigue and lots of twists and turns in a fantastical SciFi setting, I was hooked from the start and didn't put it down until I finished it.

This is actually one of my favorite choice of game books. This author really succeeds in world building. Worlds within worlds within worlds. Your goal in this series is to save Prisca from the Blot. The narrative starts on a small backwater planet with religious beliefs that encourages isolation and then expands to a galaxy with many different aliens and pocket dimensions. The imagery and plot are top notch. The characters introduced are all unique and relatable. Well-written. Highly recommend.
A great, diverse read with a lot of subtle mechanics implemented into it. Interesting from start to finish - can't wait to read the second part.
I regret buying this game. I never finished it as it got boring and it seems nothing ever actually happened. I recommend buying a different game.

This feels like a neverending prologue, like you're constantly waiting for something to happen. The author seems to punish you narratively speaking if you deviate from his desired path through the story and it's mainly because of his own politics. It doesn't feel like a choice game.
A great game book with lots of choices.
amazing storyline and definitely one i will be trying different peresonalities on later

For the price, I should have just bought and moved on to a new book. This was too short. It feels full of the promise of accomplishment, but ultimately very little happens aside from story reveals that your actions likely don't impact here. I don't plan on getting the next episode.

Zachary has a unique writing style and i love his work. The LGBT elements are not overpowering the narrative and they dont feel accessory either. It's a well crafted series that anyone with an open mind can enjoy. Can't wait to know what happened to my Hero from The Hero Project series who will be part of the next Versus interactive book.
was unsure at first but then it became so interesting definitely one to play
I love that you can be nonbinary. Ze/hir prounouns are so cool (not to mention they have a long and interesting history dating back over 20 years ago). I'd use them in real life if I could.
Truly beautiful
It was a pretty good story I thought, but it was kinda short but i enjoyed it worth the purchase.
Amazing story. I love how queer characters are included.
very enjoyable
Wow. No regrets in purchasing this story and planning to buy the series. The character, the plot, the choices were exceptional. Didn't think nothing would top the hero project but was I wrong.
I cannot put into words how much I love the Versus world and characters. There are so many ways to play this story, and I'm still discovering them all!
I really love this story, and I hope it does continue and stay as interesting as it has been in the next part of the story ! Thank you for making another great game.
Amazing story.
Such an amazing game. Loved it. <3 Can't wait for the whole story to unfold. <3 So exciting.

A really intriguing story that feels like it's constantly expanding in scope as the protagonist learns more about the world. An enjoyable narrative with choices that challenge you ethically and morally. Can't wait to read the other books

Please add an option to change the background colour, i usually only have time to read at night so the bright white background hurts my eyes a few minutes after starting to read. But other than that, i love the story. Thank you

This story is far more focused on how amazing the surrounding characters are and your own story is little more than you walking around oohing and aahing over how much greater they are than you. It seems like your actions have little impact on the flow of the story and it feels like you have to push hard against the writer to go against any character you don't like, namely for me it was the "goddess". I usually love these games but this is one I have to say does not hold up to the usual standards of Choice Of Games.

It's a decent game, but its quality is cheapened by some rather cringeworthy, annoying, and overall immersion-breaking descriptions and words. For example, the constant use of nonsensical, made-up pronouns/genders such as "Ze" and "Hir", and then the constant use of words that sound like they were made as a joke or by a toddler like "blerg" and "Blarfngard" (a curse word and location, respectively). Despite this, the story isn't too bad, and if you played it all the way through you may as well play the sequel if you're really curious about what happens. For my part, I am unsure I'll purchase the sequel or any other works from this author, as his other works appear to also be laden with this SJW drivel, something that sadly seems to be turning into something common for games released by CoG.
Really fantastic work, the way the statistics work are the best I've seen

Astounding! Took a while to warm to it. Eventually realised that this is one of the truly great interactive novels! Brilliant writing and storytelling. Choices that matter. Endless repeatability. Real depth all round.
Very well thought out. Many choices had me nervously staring at my phone, completely at a loss as to what was the best choice. Very few games make me feel the weight of my decisions like Versus did.
Effin loved it this author is the Beeze Neeze hooked

No matter how much further I read through This, it didn't intrigued me at all. There wasn't anything that interest me in the plotline :( the reviews were good but I honestly didn't find it interesting enough to keep going ...

I love the Choice Of games and have played several, but this has been my 
favorite by far! It took me a bit to get used to the complex stat system 
and wasn't initially apparent how to use it well, but a "restart" had me 
all the more engaged with what would be a top-tier sci-fi story even 
without the interactive element.
Absolutely loved it!! Can't wait to read the next installment!

An amazingly written game, very engrossing and well written. I've played

Finished the book/game in just over a day... Now I'm just waiting for the

as it was far to based around your political stance and I had a personal 
issue understanding how to read "hir" and "ze" so everytime the words were 
used it stopped the story dead for me. It was also rather frustrating to be 
told many different 5imes that my choices will effect my game play.
Well written. A fun and interesting adventure. Looking forward to more.

Was hesitant to buy out the gate, but thank goodness I did. Felt like a 
real, genuine book, with the ability to make my own choices, which is rare

clever way. Burnt through this now on to book two!

I regret buying this. It failed to connect. Normally I might have 
difficulties with beginnings due to the amount of new information but this 
game bombards me with options and information that I really don't care 
about. None of the characters, including mine, are likeable. At least not 
as far as I've been reading this. No... I've been trying to read it, 
because every time I do I have to put if away till later. The story isn't 
engaging and it seems to me like it's all about learning new worlds and 
cultures and all those boring nuances. I really don't care if the main 
character dies ion the next page. ¯\_(ツ)_/¯

In a word, excellent! Some typos, but in a story so long and well written,

Different then almost anything I've played. Truly draws you in.

I wanted to make a chaotic evil character after I finished my first playthrough, but honestly I got so bored and disencouraged after I did because the game clearly goes "you are being evil and you won't be rewarded for this.". Whereas in games like metahuman there's no clear line of good and evil. Either way it's a pretty good read with a creative story, I just wouldn't buy it again.

Holy sheit (excuse language) this is by far the best choice of game ive played for mutiple reasons i just love how it seems to start slow but it gains more and more traction and the story constantly seems to be evolving from just a simple person fighting a crazy tar creature race to discovering many more powerful and divine characters and great diplomatic choices i feel like you took the complex decison making from meta human added a very intricate and expanding plot like choice of robots and added sincere well thought out and satisfying romance similar to choice of romance its so great taking all these great aspects from other choice of games and smashing them all together to create this thing of beauty and a amazing belif/cultural decisons you can make about the game adored the game cant wait to get the second
